Document: ZIPPacker
Path: godot/classes/class_zippacker.rst
Summary: Defines the methods available for creating and manipulating ZIP archives using the ZIPPacker class.

Method: add_directory(path: String, permissions: int = 493, modified_time: int = 0) → Error
Adds a directory to the ZIP archive. The permissions and modified time can be specified.

Method: close() → Error
Closes the ZIP archive. This must be called after all files have been added.

Method: close_file() → Error
Closes the current file being written to the ZIP archive.

Method: open(path: String, append: ZipAppend = 0) → Error
Opens a ZIP archive at the specified path. The append mode determines whether to create a new archive, append to an existing one, or add to an existing archive.

Method: start_file(path: String, permissions: int = 420, modified_time: int = 0) → Error
Starts a new file within the ZIP archive. The path, permissions, and modified time can be specified.

Method: write_file(data: PackedByteArray) → Error
Writes data to the current file in the ZIP archive.

enum ZipAppend:
  APPEND_CREATE: Create a new zip archive at the given path.
  APPEND_CREATEAFTER: Append a new zip archive to the end of the already existing file at the given path.
  APPEND_ADDINZIP: Add new files to the existing zip archive at the given path.

enum CompressionLevel:
  COMPRESSION_DEFAULT: Start a file with the default Deflate compression level (6). This is a good compromise between speed and file size.
  COMPRESSION_NONE: Start a file with no compression. This is also known as the "Store" compression mode and is the fastest method of packing files inside a ZIP archive. Consider using this mode for files that are already compressed (such as JPEG, PNG, MP3, or Ogg Vorbis files).
  COMPRESSION_FAST: Start a file with the fastest Deflate compression level (1). This is fast to compress, but results in larger file sizes than COMPRESSION_DEFAULT. Decompression speed is generally unaffected by the chosen compression level.
  COMPRESSION_BEST: Start a file with the best Deflate compression level (9). This is slow to compress, but results in smaller file sizes than COMPRESSION_DEFAULT. Decompression speed is generally unaffected by the chosen compression level.
