Document: ZIPPacker
Path: godot/classes/class_zippacker.rst
Summary: Describes the methods available for creating and manipulating ZIP archives using the ZIPPacker class.

Method: add_directory(path: String, permissions: int = 493, modified_time: int = 0) → Error
Adds directory to the archive. If modified_time is set to 0, current system time is used.
Note: Directories are automatically created when start_file is called, use this function before adding files to create directories with custom permissions and modification time.

Method: close() → Error
Closes the underlying resources used by this instance.

Method: close_file() → Error
Stops writing to a file within the archive. It will fail if there is no open file.

Method: open(path: String, append: ZipAppend = 0) → Error
Opens a zip file for writing at the given path using the specified write mode. This must be called before everything else.

Method: start_file(path: String, permissions: int = 420, modified_time: int = 0) → Error
Starts writing to a file within the archive. Only one file can be written at the same time. If modified_time is set to 0, current system time is used. Must be called after open.

Method: write_file(data: PackedByteArray) → Error
Write the given data to the file. Needs to be called after start_file.